title: 1,500 Sq Ft, 2 BR 1 Bath Farm Home for Rent - Liberty Hill
posting_body: ['1,500 Sq Ft, 2 BR 1 Bath Farm Home for Rent in Liberty Hill with enclosed garage.', 'Maximum 2 occupants.', "Built in late 1800's, sits on 15 green acres, quiet and secluded.", 'Property is gated and fenced, however lease is for home and does not include use of surrounding property - no livestock, no MX tracks, no 4 wheeling, no hunting or birding.', 'Farm is equipped with water well and septic system (Upside: No water or wastewater bills; Downside: you have to know how maintain both systems).', 'Includes refrigerator, washer, dryer, stove/oven, furnished living room.', 'Equipped with evaporative cooling.', 'Any prospective tenant will have experience with care and maintenance of same.', "House was built in 1890's and was originally the Bertram train station master's home.", "The nearest neighbors are city blocks distant, and the home sits well back from the county road (about 1000' feet), so it is very tranquil.", 'There is a stock pond that stays wet most of the year with average rain.', 'Prospective tenant will provide acceptable employment and prior lease references and must have no felonies (a criminal background check will be performed).', 'Tenant must have basic to advanced carpentry/mechanical skills to handle the misc upkeep required with a 130 year old farmhouse (door handles, etc).', 'For the right tenant, will trade partial rent for carpentry work.', 'Include a Reply to Each of These Requirements With Your Inquiry / Response!', '1st and last months rent plus $950 security deposit required at lease execution.', "IMPORTANT: Interested parties - Provide Direct Email Address with your inquiry - I will not respond via Craigslist's relay system."]
